Ok. I logged on to Pendragon and have tested Charge (will test Prevent Flight too ASAP). <br>
<br>
Consider Charge to be like an extra Sprint button, on a 5-minute timer. Once you click on it, you still have to move toward your target. You will move as if you are sprinting, but at no Endurance cost. If you change targets before the 10-second limit, Charge will end. Once Charge ends, you will still move at full Sprint speed (as if you had activated Sprint), but will begin to lose Endurance normally. <br>
<br>
This ability also works in PVE. You must have something targetted to activate it. <br>
<br>
IMO it is probably worth it to put 5 points toward this ability. It will probably work well with Tireless and Longwind. <br>
<br>
That's all I have to report for now. <br>
<br>
<br>
Edit: You can target anything (friendly players, grave stones etc.) to activate Charge. Charge can be used to run away from people/mobs. You just have to remain targetting the same person while it's on. <br>
